President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key positions at the U.S. Department of State. Daniel J. Kritenbrink is nominated for Assistant Secretary of State for East Asian and Pacific Affairs. Kritenbrink, currently serving as the U.S. Ambassador to Vietnam, has extensive experience in Asian affairs and speaks fluent Chinese and Japanese. Brian A. Nichols is nominated for Assistant Secretary of State for Western Hemisphere Affairs. Nichols, currently serving as the U.S. Ambassador to Zimbabwe, previously served as the U.S. Ambassador to Peru and has a strong background in international narcotics and law enforcement affairs. Brett M. Holmgren is nominated for Assistant Secretary of State for Intelligence and Research. Holmgren, who previously worked in various roles in the intelligence and security fields, most recently served as the Deputy for Nominations for the Biden-Harris Transition Team. These nominations reflect President Biden's commitment to assembling a diverse and experienced team to tackle key foreign policy challenges.